[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stephen McLaughlin and Dru Yearwood sign new Southend deals

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Southend United midfielders Stephen McLaughlin and Dru Yearwood have both signed new contracts with the League One club.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
McLaughlin, 27, who initially joined on loan from Nottingham Forest in 2015, has signed a three-year contract.
He helped the Blues to promotion via the play-offs in his first season and made the move permanent in August 2015.
The Irishman told Southend's website: "Now I know my future I can really look forward to the next few years."
Yearwood, 17, joined Southend at the age of 11 and has signed a four-year deal after impressing during pre-season training with the first team.
